This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as keyword generation. It also involves the use of generative neural networks, which is a common technique in NLP research. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) because it addresses challenges in sponsored search, which is a subfield of information retrieval. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because it involves the use of machine learning techniques such as reinforcement learning and generative models. 

Finally, it could be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision) because the proposed model aims to improve ad impressions, which is a visual task. However, this is less likely than the other categories mentioned above.
